<p>In the latest development, Greenland’s party leaders publicly rejected President Trump’s renewed push to bring the Arctic island under US control, saying Greenland’s future must be decided by Greenlanders. The push has unsettled European governments because Greenland is an autonomous territory within the Kingdom of Denmark, and Denmark is a NATO ally. Some media reports also say Trump has asked US military planners for contingency options, while other accounts emphasize that senior US military officials have raised legal and political objections.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/uS2Idh6e2Agn-u_XYLGn4uWKQ3tTD40zJgO1QrRkcqEgEgxeKx48EjtFsPp6mbtaKLxW5qBH49Ur1v7iujDsNKhoxW_GuSR6D80jT9OV2oSR' alt='A woman walks past Greenland’s parliament Inatsisartut in Nuuk, Greenland on March 28, 2025.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>What Trump says: President Trump said the US would act on Greenland “whether they like it or not,” framing the issue around security and competition with Russia and China.</li><li>Europe’s anxiety: European concern has risen further after the reported US incursion in Venezuela last weekend, which NPR says sharpened worries about Washington’s willingness to use force abroad.</li><li>Nato messaging: European allies have been rattled by NATO’s lack of a public statement explicitly backing Denmark’s territorial integrity regarding Greenland, according to the Financial Times.</li><li>Danish warning: Denmark’s Prime Minister Mette Frederiksen warned that an American takeover of Greenland would mark the end of NATO, Firstpost reported.</li><li>Reported pushback: Reports say senior US military leadership has resisted invasion planning on legal grounds and because of congressional support concerns.</li></ul><blockquote>We don’t want to be Ame­ricans, we don’t want to be Danish, we want to be Gre­en­landers - Leaders of five parties in Greenland’s parliament</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Greenland’s parliamentary party leaders: They say Greenlanders alone should decide the island’s future and reject outside pressure over sovereignty. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/greenland-trump-reject-acquisition-dont-want-to-be-americans/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>President Donald Trump (United States): He argues the US needs control of Greenland for security reasons and has not ruled out coercive measures, according to multiple reports. (<a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/video/greenland-rejects-trumps-threats-one-lawmaker-saying-not-product-people/'>CBS News</a>)</li><li>European governments and institutions: They view the rhetoric as destabilizing for transatlantic security and worry about its implications for NATO unity. (<a href='https://www.npr.org/2026/01/10/nx-s1-5673112/europe-alarmed-by-trumps-greenland-push'>NPR</a>)</li><li>US military leadership (reported): Senior officers have reportedly questioned the legality and political feasibility of planning an operation to seize Greenland. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/trump-asked-us-special-forces-to-plan-greenland-invasion-faces-resistance-from-military-generals-report-13967597.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.cbsnews.com/news/greenland-trump-reject-acquisition-dont-want-to-be-americans/'>Greenland&#x27;s leaders reject Trump push: &quot;We don&#x27;t want to be Americans&quot;</a> - cbsnews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/630802-trump-plan-invade-greenland/'>Trump orders plan to invade Greenland – media</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1966293/we-dont-want-to-be-americans-greenland-says-after-latest-trump-threat'>‘We don’t want to be Americans’, Greenland says after latest Trump threat</a> - dawn.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/trump-asked-us-special-forces-to-plan-greenland-invasion-faces-resistance-from-military-generals-report-13967597.html'>Trump asked US special forces to plan Greenland invasion, faces resistance from military generals: Re